nodes.documentation:
@title ChronoBank Asset implementation contract.
 * Basic asset implementation contract, without any additional logic.
Every other asset implementation contracts should derive from this one.
Receives calls from the proxy, and calls back immediatly without arguments modification.
 * Note: all the non constant functions return false instead of throwing in case if state change
didn't happen yet.
nodes.name: ChronoBankAsset

nodes.documentation: Only assigned proxy is allowed to call.
nodes.name: onlyProxy

nodes.documentation: Only assets's admins are allowed to execute
nodes.name: onlyAuthorized

nodes.documentation:
Sets asset proxy address.
     * Can be set only once.
     * @param _proxy asset proxy contract address.
     * @return success.
@dev function is final, and must not be overridden.
nodes.name: init

nodes.documentation: @dev Lifts the ban on transfers for given addresses
nodes.name: restrict

nodes.documentation: @dev Revokes the ban on transfers for given addresses
nodes.name: unrestrict

nodes.documentation:
@dev called by the owner to pause, triggers stopped state
Only admin is allowed to execute this method.
nodes.name: pause

nodes.documentation:
@dev called by the owner to unpause, returns to normal state
Only admin is allowed to execute this method.
nodes.name: unpause

nodes.documentation:
Passes execution into virtual function.
     * Can only be called by assigned asset proxy.
     * @return success.
@dev function is final, and must not be overridden.
nodes.name: __transferWithReference

nodes.documentation:
Calls back without modifications if an asset is not stopped.
Checks whether _from/_sender are not in blacklist.
     * @return success.
@dev function is virtual, and meant to be overridden.
